The paper deals with computational geometry and combinatorics, specifically the problem of stabbing convex sets and variants of the Hadwiger-Debrunner theorem. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves algorithmic techniques and data structures, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as another likely sub-category. The use of combinatorial methods and discrete structures in the paper may also make it relevant to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper involves theoretical results and complexity analysis, which may make it relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
